ty and ethics. Contributors offer new, expansive perspectives on atheism’s diverse history and possible futures. By recovering lines of affinity and tension between particular atheists and particular religious traditions, this book paves the way for fruitful conversation between religious and non-religious people in our secular age.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAtheism and literaturevCongresses. 0aAtheismvCongresses. 0aChristianity and atheismvCongresses. 7aRELIGION / General.2bisacsh  achristopher hitchens, richard dawkins, sam harris, ethics, community, feeling, imagination, religion, spirituality, secularism, belief, faith, agnosticism, sociology, anthropology, collective, culture, nonfiction, christianity, god, monotheism, pagan, alternative, world, geography, sacred, holy, tradition, history, intellectualism, science, rationality.1 aFurey, Constance M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMontemaggi, Vittorio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewheiser, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewheiser, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPattison, George, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRubenstein, Mary- Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSingh, Devin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTegtmeyer, Henning, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTicciati, Susannah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Denys, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWillis, Andre C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dD